// C3: Physical sensing components
instance MotorPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "High-resolution incremental/absolute encoder mounted directly on the permanent magnet synchronous motor providing positional feedback for closed-loop control. Implements industrial-grade standards with sub-micrometer resolution."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorPositionDataTransmitted
]

instance GearboxPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Secondary high-resolution encoder positioned behind the gearbox providing additional positional feedback for motion control validation. Implements industrial-grade standards with sub-micrometer resolution."
    DTDFVocab:producedData GearboxPositionDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance MotorPositionDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorPositionEncoder
    base:desc "Time-series positional data stream from motor encoder transmitted via MQTT protocol with low-latency requirements for real-time processing."
]

instance GearboxPositionDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom GearboxPositionEncoder
    base:desc "Time-series positional data stream from gearbox encoder transmitted via MQTT protocol with low-latency requirements for real-time processing."
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance PositionalFeedbackData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated and preprocessed positional data traces from both motor and gearbox encoders, normalized and filtered for quality assurance before model consumption."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorPositionDataTransmitted, GearboxPositionDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PositionalModelEnabler, DigitalShadowAggregator
]

instance MechanicalSystemModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML Internal Block Diagram representing the mechanical architecture of the motor-gearbox assembly with component-connector relationships for structural analysis."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulationIntegrationEnabler
]

instance ControlSystemModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML state machine model of the Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl controller behavior with position/speed/acceleration state transitions."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ControlSimulationEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance DigitalShadowAggregator : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Passive data aggregation component implementing the Digital Shadow Reference Model (UML class diagram) for one-way automated data flow from physical to virtual representation."
    DTDFVocab:enables DigitalShadowVisualizationService, DataAbstractionService
]

instance PositionalModelEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MontiArc-based component processing positional data traces to update the mechanical system model in real-time using SysML IBD composition hierarchies."
    DTDFVocab:enables PositionalAnalysisService
]

instance SimulationIntegrationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Tool interoperability framework enabling bidirectional data exchange between SysML IBD models and MathWorks Simulink for behavioral simulation."
    DTDFVocab:enables SimulationService
]

instance ControlSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MontiArc Automaton integration with Simulink for executing control system state machines with real-time constraints."
    DTDFVocab:enables ControlValidationService
]

instance MQTTDataProcessor : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MQTT protocol handler for low-latency sensor data ingestion with preprocessing capabilities (filtering, normalization) before model consumption."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataQualityService
]

// C6: Services
instance DigitalShadowVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Passive visualization service rendering UML-based reference models of system states and relationships without active control capabilities."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemStateInsight
]

instance DataAbstractionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Contextual data trace aggregation service creating baseline representations for future Digital Twin development without active processing."
    DTDFVocab:provides DataBaselineInsight
]

instance PositionalAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time positional data analysis service validating mechanical alignment and encoder synchronization within specified torque/velocity limits."
    DTDFVocab:provides MechanicalAlignmentInsight
]

instance SimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Behavioral simulation service executing SysML models in MathWorks Simulink environment for dynamic system response analysis."
    DTDFVocab:provides SimulationResultInsight
]

instance ControlValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Control system validation service executing state machine models against real-time operational constraints from the Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl controller."
    DTDFVocab:provides ControlComplianceInsight
]

instance DataQualityService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Data preprocessing service ensuring quality and relevance of MQTT-transmitted sensor data through filtering and normalization."
    DTDFVocab:provides DataQualityInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance SystemStateInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Passive representation of current system states and relationships through UML-based visualization without active interpretation."
]

instance DataBaselineInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Aggregated baseline data traces for manufacturing process identification and future Digital Twin development foundation."
]

instance MechanicalAlignmentInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation of mechanical alignment between motor and gearbox components within operational torque/velocity constraints."
]

instance SimulationResultInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Dynamic system response analysis results from SysML-Simulink integrated behavioral simulations."
]

instance ControlComplianceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation results of control system behavior against Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl controller specifications and safety protocols."
]

instance DataQualityInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Quality metrics and preprocessing results for MQTT-transmitted sensor data streams."
]

// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Primary actuation component driven by Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl controller accepting position/speed/acceleration inputs with torque/velocity limitations."
]

instance GearTransmissionAssembly : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Mechanical gearbox assembly coupled with the permanent magnet synchronous motor determining actuation ranges and mechanical specifications."
]

instance SiemensSINUMERIK840DslController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Industrial automation controller governing robot actuation with position/speed/acceleration command execution and emergency stop protocols."
]

// C10: Additional Models/Data
instance SafetyConstraintModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML logical architecture model defining torque/velocity limits and emergency stop protocols for industrial safety compliance."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SafetyValidationEnabler
]

instance ActuationRangeModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Mechanical specification model defining operational ranges for the motor-gearbox assembly based on physical constraints."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo RangeValidationEnabler
]

// C11: Additional Enablers
instance SafetyValidationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MontiArc Automaton implementation validating real-time adherence to safety constraints during operation."
    DTDFVocab:enables SafetyComplianceService
]

instance RangeValidationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Component validating actuation ranges against mechanical specification models during operation."
    DTDFVocab:enables RangeComplianceService
]

// C6: Additional Services
instance SafetyComplianceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time validation service ensuring adherence to torque/velocity limits and emergency stop protocols."
    DTDFVocab:provides SafetyComplianceInsight
]

instance RangeComplianceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating current actuation parameters against mechanical specification ranges."
    DTDFVocab:provides RangeComplianceInsight
]

// C17: Additional Insights
instance SafetyComplianceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time validation results of safety protocol adherence during system operation."
]

instance RangeComplianceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation results of current actuation parameters against mechanical specification ranges."
]

// C1: Environment
instance ManufacturingDigitalTwinEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Industrial manufacturing environment hosting the Digital Twin system with heterogeneous stakeholder integration."
    base:contains PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor,
                GearTransmissionAssembly,
                SiemensSINUMERIK840DslController,
                MotorPositionEncoder,
                GearboxPositionEncoder,
                DigitalShadowAggregator,
                PositionalModelEnabler,
                SimulationIntegrationEnabler
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system operates with a **real-time, data-driven temporal synchronization** between the physical and digital components, leveraging **live data streams** from sensors. While the document does not specify exact synchronization frequencies or latency requirements, it implies a **time-series-based approach** where sensor data (e.g., from manufacturing systems) is continuously streamed via **MQTT** for near-instantaneous updates. The temporal granularity is dictated by the **real-time operational needs** of the physical system, ensuring the digital representation reflects the current state with minimal delay. No explicit mention of discrete time scales for different services is provided, but the emphasis on 'live' and 'real-time' suggests a **high-frequency, low-latency** interaction paradigm, aligned with the Digital Shadow's one-way data flow but extended by the Digital Twin's active processing capabilities."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The **Digital Twin constellation** is orchestrated through **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** frameworks, leveraging **multi-notation modeling** (e.g., **SysML for architecture**, **Simulink or other simulation tools for behavior**, and **general-purpose languages like C++/Java for implementation**). The **architecture patterns** are defined using **architecture description languages (ADLs)** such as **ACME, AADL, or MontiArc**, which provide **component-based decomposition**, **interface definitions**, and **composition rules**. **Resource management** is implicitly handled via **tool-specific execution environments** (e.g., **Simulink’s runtime** or **MontiArc’s automaton-based coordination**). **System-wide coordination** is achieved through **behavioral modeling** (e.g., **state machines in SysML v1.7** or **MontiArc Automaton**) and **integration with simulation tools** to ensure **consistent synchronization** between digital and physical layers. The **orchestration** may also involve **heterogeneous stakeholder perspectives**, requiring **model transformation** or **ontology alignment** to maintain coherence across tools [17]–[30]."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle stages in the provided context are structured through **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** methodologies, which decompose system modeling into **four hierarchical abstraction layers**: **requirements** (high-level system objectives), **functional architecture** (decomposition into functional components), **logical architecture** (abstract component interactions via architecture description languages like **ACME**, **AADL**, or **MontiArc**), and **product/technical layer** (physical implementation details). Transition management between these phases is facilitated by **methodologies such as RFLP (Requirements, Functions, Logics, Physics)**, **OOSEM**, **SPES**, or **SMArDT**, which ensure consistency across layers. Behavioral modeling (e.g., state machines in **SysML v1.7** or **MontiArc Automaton**) integrates with simulation tools like **MathWorks Simulink** or general-purpose languages (**C++/Java**) to refine system behavior. Lifecycle governance is implied through **heterogeneous stakeholder integration**, requiring alignment of diverse modeling notations and tools to maintain coherence across phases."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system incorporates **fidelity and validity considerations** through structured **validation and verification (V&V) processes**, though specific methodologies are not detailed in the provided document. Key aspects include:
  - **Model fidelity requirements** are implicitly tied to the **abstraction layers** (e.g., functional vs. physical) and the **precision of modeling languages/tools** (e.g., SysML for logical architecture, Simulink for behavioral simulation). Fidelity is ensured by **cross-tool consistency checks** (e.g., aligning SysML IBDs with Simulink models).
  - **Uncertainty sources** arise from **data abstraction in digital shadows** (e.g., aggregated sensor traces) and **model approximations** (e.g., state machines vs. continuous-time simulations). Quantification of uncertainty may rely on **statistical methods** or **simulation-based error propagation**, though no explicit techniques are cited.
  - **Error detection and correction mechanisms** are not explicitly described, but the integration of **heterogeneous tools** (e.g., SysML + Simulink) suggests **automated or semi-automated validation pipelines** (e.g., model transformation checks, simulation-to-model traceability).
  - **Quality assurance processes** are implied by the **MBSE framework**, which enforces **traceability across abstraction layers** (e.g., requirements → functions → logic → physics) and **stakeholder-specific perspectives**. However, no concrete QA protocols (e.g., ISO standards, formal verification) are referenced."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system integrates horizontally with **external systems** primarily through **one-way data flows** (as defined in the Digital Shadow Reference Model), where sensor data is **streamed via MQTT** from physical objects to the digital representation. While the document does not specify exact interoperability standards beyond MQTT, it implies **protocol-based communication** for real-time data ingestion. Dependencies on external systems are managed via **MBSE tools** (e.g., SysML, Simulink) that support **multi-notation transformations** (e.g., SysML to Simulink for simulation). However, the document does not detail **API-based communication**, **enterprise system integration patterns**, or **federated Digital Twin orchestration**. The focus remains on **sensor-to-Digital Twin data pipelines** with minimal explicit mention of broader system-of-systems integration."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The provided context references **SysML [17]**, **ACME [23]**, **AADL [24]**, and **MontiArc [25], [26]** as standardized modeling languages for **architecture description** and **behavioral modeling**, but does not explicitly list **industry standards, specifications, or certification frameworks**. Compliance is implied through adherence to **MBSE methodologies** (e.g., RFLP, OOSEM) and **interoperability** via **ADLs** and **simulation tools (Simulink)**. No explicit mention of **ISO/IEC 19505, SAE AS5506, or ISO 15288** is provided; only citation numbers ([17], [24]) are referenced without standard titles."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "The provided documents mention **Asset Administration Shell (AAS)** as a framework for integrating and managing digital twins within Industrie 4.0, but they do not specify security protocols (e.g., OAuth 2.0, JWT) or detailed cybersecurity measures. The **MABI robotic system** (Document [44]) references a **safety cell** for physical safety, indicating a basic safety mechanism for human-machine interaction, but no technical details on fail-safe mechanisms, risk assessment approaches (e.g., ISO 31000, IEC 61508), or safety-critical system considerations (e.g., ISO 26262) are provided. The **MQTT protocol** (Document [52]) is referenced for data streaming, but its security implementation (e.g., TLS, authentication) is not described. No evidence of access control mechanisms, threat mitigation strategies, or compliance with cybersecurity standards (e.g., IEC 62443) is found in the documents."
]